# Frontend Standards

## TypeScript

- Strict typing always. **Never use `any`**.
- All shared types live in `frontend/src/types/index.ts`.

## React

- Functional components only. No class components.
- Single-purpose, isolated components. One component = one responsibility.
- Declarative — derive UI from state, no imperative DOM manipulation.
- State management via **Zustand** (web). Design state to be translatable to Riverpod (Flutter).

## Tech Stack

- React + TypeScript + Vite + Tailwind CSS v4
- Routing: React Router (`Link`, `useNavigate`)
- State: Zustand stores

## Examples

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — any, imperative, mixed concerns
const handle = (e: any) => { document.getElementById('x')!.style.display = 'none'; }

// ✅ GOOD — typed, declarative, single-purpose
const [isVisible, setIsVisible] = useState(true);
const handleClose = () => setIsVisible(false);
```
